		<div id="unique-entry-id-413" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Seven Stories Pirate Week</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 28 May 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-books.php">Books</a></span><span class="blog-entry-category"> <a href="category-pirates.php">Pirates</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></div>Are you in Newcastle Upon Tyne near Ouseburn Valley.  Well Seven Stories on Lime Street has Pirate Week this Spring Half Term.  Please see http://www.sevenstories.org.uk/whats-on/pirate-week-this-spring-half-term-e48909 for more details.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-412" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Twitter and Blackbeard</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 28 May 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>If you don&rsquo;t follow Justin Somper (@JustinSomper) on Twitter here are some reasons to get a twitter account and follow him.<br /><br />&ldquo;Blackbeard's anchor lifted from Davy Jones's Locker <a href="http://bbc.in/lLUaDP" rel="self">http://bbc.in/lLUaDP</a>&rdquo;<br /><br />&rdquo;Excited to hear they've found Blackbeard's anchor - more than 1000 kg of pirate history!&rdquo;<br /><br />&ldquo;Review of @JustinSomper's Immortal War - A fitting conclusion to the series. Nocturnals get ready!! @simonkids_UK - <a href="http://bit.ly/kVjhzZ" rel="self">http://bit.ly/kVjhzZ</a>&rdquo;<br /><br />&ldquo;@empireofbooks @simonkids_UK Thanks for the first official review of IMMORTAL WAR, Ryan! Couldn't be more thrilled with your verdict.&rdquo;<br /><br />&ldquo;I'm on a mission to have 1000 followers by June 9th - publication day of IMMORTAL WAR. Can you help?&rdquo;<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-409" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Vampirates Book 6 The Immortal War Publication Dates</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 25 May 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="Immortal War" src="ImmortalWar.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></div><h5>Vampirates Book 6 The Immortal War</h5><br />Will be published in the UK&nbsp;on&nbsp;9&nbsp;June 2011<br />Simon & Schuster UK Ltd&nbsp;/ ISBN-10: 1416916547&nbsp;/ ISBN-13: 978-1416916543&nbsp;<br /><br />Will be&nbsp;published in the USA&nbsp;on 2 January 2012<br />Little, Brown Books for Young Readers / ISBN-10: 0316033243&nbsp;/ ISBN-13: 978-0316033244<br /><br />To read a selected text from the first two chapters please see <a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/the-books/samplechapterimmortalwar/" rel="self" title="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/the-books/samplechapterimmortalwar/">http://www.vampirates.co.uk/the-books/samplechapterimmortalwar/</a><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-408" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Signed Copies</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 25 May 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-right"><img class="imageStyle" alt="Blog Tour" src="BlogTour.jpg" width="213" height="539" /></div><h5>For a signed copy of Immortal war please contact these independent bookshops:</h5><br />Steyning Bookshop, 106 High Street, Steyning, West Sussex, BN44 3RD<br />Phone: 01903 812062<br />&nbsp;<br />Victoria Park Books&nbsp;, 174 Victoria Park Road, City of London, Greater London E9 7HD<br />Phone: 020 8986 1124<br />&nbsp;<br />Pritchards, 54 Brows Lane, Liverpool, Merseyside L37 4ED<br />Phone: 01704 875765<br />&nbsp;<br />Waterstones Oldham, 46/47 The Spindles Centre, GB - Oldham OL1 1HD<br />Phone: 0843 290 8531<br />&nbsp;<br />Silverdell Books, 61 Poulton St. Kirkham, Preston, PR4 2AJ&nbsp;<br />Phone: 01772 683444<br />&nbsp;<br />Simply Books, 228 Moss Lane, Bramhall, Cheshire, SK7 1BD<br />Phone: 0161 4391436<br />&nbsp;<br />Newham Bookshop, 745-747 Barking Road, London E13 9ER<br />Phone: 020 8552 9993<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-407" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Blog Tour</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 25 May 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span><span class="blog-entry-category"> <a href="category-tour.php">Tour</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="Blog Tour" src="BlogTour.jpg" width="213" height="539" /></div>So no one is left out here is a copy of the blog tour, set up by the folks at S&S and sent to me by the Captain so everyone gets the chance to see it.<br /><br />Monday 6th June - Chicklish - Extract #1 (<a href="http://keris.typepad.com/chicklet/2011/05/news-vampirates-immortal-war-blog-tour.html" rel="self" title="http://keris.typepad.com/chicklet/2011/05/news-vampirates-immortal-war-blog-tour.html">http://keris.typepad.com/chicklet/</a>)<br />Tuesday 7th June - My Favourite Books - An interview with Justin Somper (<a href="http://myfavouritebooks.blogspot.com/p/blog-tours-2011.html" rel="self" title="http://myfavouritebooks.blogspot.com/p/blog-tours-2011.html">http://myfavouritebooks.blogspot.com/</a>)<br />Wednesday 8th June - The Crooked Shelf - The Women of Vampirates (<a href="http://thecrookedshelf.blogspot.com/" rel="self" title="http://thecrookedshelf.blogspot.com/">http://thecrookedshelf.blogspot.com/</a>) (SM I think I cannot find any comment about it).<br />Thursday 9th June - Feeling Fictional - Animal Antics (<a href="http://www.feelingfictional.com/2011/05/news-vampirates-blog-tour-with-justin.html" rel="self" title="http://www.feelingfictional.com/2011/05/news-vampirates-blog-tour-with-justin.html">http://www.feelingfictional.com/</a>)<br />Friday 10th June - The Bookette - Extract #2 (<a href="http://www.thebookette.co.uk/" rel="self" title="http://www.thebookette.co.uk/">http://www.thebookette.co.uk/</a>)<br />Saturday 11th June - Girls Without A Bookshelf - Playlists & The Music of Vampirates (<a href="http://withoutabookshelf.blogspot.com/" rel="self" title="http://withoutabookshelf.blogspot.com/">http://withoutabookshelf.blogspot.com/</a>)<br />Sunday 12th June - Wondrous Reads - 10 Ways to Know You're Obsessed with Vampirates (<a href="http://www.wondrousreads.com/2011/05/news-justin-sompers-vampirates-blog.html" rel="self" title="http://www.wondrousreads.com/2011/05/news-justin-sompers-vampirates-blog.html">http://www.wondrousreads.com/</a>)<br />Monday 13th June - Daisy Chain Books - Ending An Era: Killing Off Vampirates (<a href="http://daisychainbookreviews.blogspot.com/" rel="self" title="http://daisychainbookreviews.blogspot.com/">http://daisychainbookreviews.blogspot.com/</a>)<br />Tuesday 14th June - Empire of Books - Top ten Vampirates characters ever (<a href="http://empire-of-books.blogspot.com/" rel="self" title="http://empire-of-books.blogspot.com/">http://empire-of-books.blogspot.com/</a>)<br />Wednesday 15th June - Book Zone For Boys -- Q&A with Justin (<a href="http://bookzone4boys.blogspot.com/" rel="self" title="http://bookzone4boys.blogspot.com/">http://bookzone4boys.blogspot.com/</a>)<br />Thursday 16th June - I Want To Read That - WIN! Vampirates swag (<a href="http://www.iwanttoreadthat.com/" rel="self" title="http://www.iwanttoreadthat.com/">http://www.iwanttoreadthat.com/</a>)<br /><br />Later in June, Justin will be touring around the UK for real on an exciting one week tour through London, Liverpool, Oldham, Lancashire and Cheshire.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-406" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Blogs</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 18 May 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-tempesttwins.php">TempestTwins</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="mouse" src="mouse.jpg" width="41" height="41" /></div>Justin's Blog may be up but mine will not publish.  (Sorry the last one appears not to have either).  I am working on it.<br /><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-405" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">BLOG Its up</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 18 May 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>I see Vampirates.co.uk VIP section has now been updated.  There is a new blog by Justin Somper.  I got a mention (very happy here).<br />"I caught up with another valued crew-mate, Ship&rsquo;s Mouse, at the Oxford Literary Festival in April."<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-403" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Twitter Nuggets</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Thursday, 12 May 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span><span class="blog-entry-category"> <a href="category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="ImmortalWar.jpg" src="Immortal War.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></div>The Immortal War arrives in Paperback on 9th June 2011 in the UK and as you can see from the tweet below the United States and Canada get theirs six months later.<br /><br />"Looking forward to returning to Warwick Uni for first time in 21 (!) years - to talk at Alumni Knowledge Exchange Day on May 21st."<br /><br />"Thanks for your tweet. IMMORTAL WAR will be published in the US in January 2012."<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-404" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">No Blog Yet.</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 07 May 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>I know I am not finding much at the moment.  I notice even under Stop Press the Vampirates.co.uk staff have written "You Nocturnals are not the only ones starting to wonder!" about the fact Justin Somper has been too busy writing Immortal War to publish a blog.  I think getting my hands on a copy of the book is more important to me, then Grace's Crossing Stories than a blog so I will sit and wait a bit longer.  Only about a month to go.<br /></div></div>
	</div>
	
	 
